princeton_ansible.title: pulbot is failing to deploy applications on `appdeploy1`

comments.body:
Querying for the logs yields that the logs were rotated before this failure occurred:

```bash
pulsys@appdeploy1:/var/log$ sudo systemctl status networking.service
● networking.service - Raise network interfaces
   Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/networking.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)
   Active: failed (Result: exit-code) since Thu 2021-07-15 15:41:15 UTC; 8 months 0 days ago
     Docs: man:interfaces(5)
 Main PID: 464 (code=exited, status=1/FAILURE)

Warning: Journal has been rotated since unit was started. Log output is incomplete or unavailable.
```

Requests to deploy an application yield the following `hubot` logs:

```bash
[Wed Mar 16 2022 18:36:52 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time)] INFO { id: 'hubot-deploy.create', hubotDeployAuthenticate: true }
```

3 minutes passed following this, and no further activity was logged.

The `redis` server (which is deployed locally for `heaven`) may likely to be the cause of the delays for deployments:

```bash
32744:M 16 Mar 18:32:57.029 * 10 changes in 300 seconds. Saving...
32744:M 16 Mar 18:32:57.032 * Background saving started by pid 22836
22836:C 16 Mar 18:32:57.167 * DB saved on disk
22836:C 16 Mar 18:32:57.169 * RDB: 0 MB of memory used by copy-on-write
32744:M 16 Mar 18:32:57.232 * Background saving terminated with success
32744:M 16 Mar 18:37:58.090 * 10 changes in 300 seconds. Saving...
32744:M 16 Mar 18:37:58.093 * Background saving started by pid 23279
23279:C 16 Mar 18:37:58.230 * DB saved on disk
23279:C 16 Mar 18:37:58.232 * RDB: 0 MB of memory used by copy-on-write
32744:M 16 Mar 18:37:58.294 * Background saving terminated with success
32744:M 16 Mar 18:42:59.045 * 10 changes in 300 seconds. Saving...
32744:M 16 Mar 18:42:59.048 * Background saving started by pid 23698
23698:C 16 Mar 18:42:59.191 * DB saved on disk
23698:C 16 Mar 18:42:59.193 * RDB: 0 MB of memory used by copy-on-write
32744:M 16 Mar 18:42:59.251 * Background saving terminated with success
```

From what I could best determine, this somehow relates to a queue of `redis` jobs enqueued by `resque`. Restarting `appdeploy-workers` with the following resolved this:

```bash
pulsys@appdeploy1:/opt/appdeploy/current/log$ sudo systemctl  restart appdeploy-workers.service
```

The following `systemd` service configuration is invoking `resque`:

```bash
[Unit]
Description=manage resque worker instances as a service, instance %i
Requires=appdeploy-workers.service
Before=appdeploy-workers.service
BindsTo=appdeploy-workers.service

[Service]
PermissionsStartOnly=true
Type=idle
User=deploy
Group=deploy
UMask=0002
WorkingDirectory=/opt/pulbot/current
ExecStart=/bin/bash --login -c "/usr/local/bin/bundle exec rake resque:work QUEUE=* RAILS_ENV=production"
RestartSec=1
Restart=on-failure
StandardOutput=syslog
StandardError=syslog
SyslogIdentifier=resque

[Install]
WantedBy=appdeploy-workers.service
```

...and it seems as if this was updated by `ansible` at some point during 03/15/22:

```bash
pulsys@appdeploy1:/opt/appdeploy/current/log$ sudo grep --color -r resque /var/log/syslog.1
Mar 15 11:35:43 appdeploy1 ansible-ansible.legacy.copy: Invoked with src=/home/pulsys/.ansible/tmp/ansible-tmp-1647344145.4215791-6497-116872363878722/source directory_mode=None force=True remote_src=None unsafe_writes=False checksum=b49166528e9fbbf8a61f345a562b3a5531a9d64a seuser=None _original_basename=resque-start.sh serole=None content=NOT_LOGGING_PARAMETER dest=/usr/bin/appdeploy-workers-start.sh setype=None follow=False mode=508 selevel=None owner=None group=None validate=None attributes=None backup=False local_follow=None
Mar 15 11:36:17 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Stopped manages resque workers as a single service.
Mar 15 11:36:17 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Stopping manages resque workers as a single service...
Mar 15 11:36:17 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Stopping manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 2...
Mar 15 11:36:17 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Stopping manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 1...
Mar 15 11:36:17 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Stopping manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 3...
Mar 15 11:36:18 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Stopped manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 2.
Mar 15 11:36:18 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Started manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 2.
Mar 15 11:36:18 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Stopped manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 3.
Mar 15 11:36:18 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Started manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 3.
Mar 15 11:36:21 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Stopped manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 1.
Mar 15 11:36:21 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Started manage resque worker instances as a service, instance 1.
Mar 15 11:36:21 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Starting manages resque workers as a single service...
Mar 15 11:36:21 appdeploy1 systemd[1]: Started manages resque workers as a single service.
```
As it was confirmed that an `ansible` client ran the `playbook` yesterday, I am going to conclude that this was a failure to restart the `appdeploy-workers` service following this `playbook` run.

As https://github.com/pulibrary/pul-the-hard-way/issues/107 is the actionable solution, I am going to proceed with closing this (unless it occurs once again, and the proposed solution fails to resolve this problem).

pulfalight.title: Add a rake task to delete an EAD from the index

comments.body:
Example of deleting without rake task:

```
irb(main):001:0> Blacklight.default_index.connection
=> #<RSolr::Client:0x00005573102d2430 @uri=#<URI::HTTP http://lib-solr8-prod.princeton.edu:8983/solr/pulfalight-production/>, @proxy=nil, @connection=nil, @update_format=RSolr::JSON::Generator, @update_path="update", @options={:adapter=>nil, :url=>"http://lib-solr8-prod.princeton.edu:8983/solr/pulfalight-production"}>
irb(main):002:0> Blacklight.default_index.connection.delete_by_id("AC107")
=> {"responseHeader"=>{"rf"=>3, "status"=>0, "QTime"=>2}}
irb(main):003:0> Blacklight.default_index.connection.commit
```

The rake task should output a message like "If you run this rake task, ask the person who needed a finding aid deleted to please first unpublish the EAD, wait for it to disappear in findingaids, and then delete it."
